  "prompt": "If any unknown person complaint FIR (not name in FIR) against me then what I should do?",
  "response": "If an FIR (First Information Report) is lodged against you by an unknown person, it is important to take the following steps:\n\n1. **Stay Calm**: Try to remain composed and avoid panicking. It\u2019s crucial to approach the situation logically and legally.\n\n2. **Obtain a Copy of the FIR**: You have the right to get a copy of the FIR. You can request this from the police station where the FIR has been filed. This will help you understand the allegations against you.\n\n3. **Consult a Lawyer**: Seek legal advice from a qualified lawyer who specializes in criminal law. They can guide you through the legal process, explain your rights, and help you build a defense strategy.\n\n4. **Understand the Allegations**: Carefully review the FIR with your lawyer to understand the specific allegations and charges against you.\n\n5. **Gather Evidence and Witnesses**: Start collecting any evidence or identifying witnesses that can support your innocence or provide relevant information regarding the incident.\n\n6. **File for Anticipatory Bail**: If there is a risk of arrest, your lawyer may advise you to file for anticipatory bail to prevent arrest and detention.\n\n7. **Prepare Your Defense**: Work with your lawyer to prepare a strong defense. This may include gathering documentary evidence, alibi witnesses, or any other relevant proof.\n\n8. **Respond to Police Notices**: If you receive any notices or summons from the police, ensure you respond promptly and cooperate with the investigation.\n\n9. **Attend Court Hearings**: If the case proceeds to court, make sure to attend all hearings and follow your lawyer\u2019s advice diligently.\n\n10. **Avoid Contact with the Complainant**: Refrain from contacting the complainant or engaging in any activity that could be construed as tampering with evidence or witnesses.\n\n11. **Maintain Documentation**: Keep thorough records of all communications, legal documents, and interactions related to the case.\n\nRemember, the legal process can be complex, and it\u2019s essential to have professional guidance to navigate through it effectively.",
